{
    "comments": [
        {
            "type": {
                "id": 205,
                "en": "Reason the facility does not meet the criteria for NPRI",
                "fr": "La raison pour laquelle cette installation ne rencontre pas les critères de déclaration de l'INRP"
            },
            "comment": "Calgary Landfill didn’t meet the NPRI screening criteria for assessing Part 1A or 1B substances,\r\nsince employees at the facility worked less than 20,000 hours in 2022. Facility records indicate that\r\non-site releases to air, water, or land and off-site transfers of all NPRI contaminants listed in Part 1A\r\nand 1B were below the NPRI Manufacture, Process, or Otherwise used (MPO) thresholds.\r\nThe facility did not incidentally manufacture any of the listed PAHs in NPRI Part 2; therefore, reporting\r\nunder NPRI Part 2 was not required.\r\nThe facility was not engaged in the listed activities in Part 3; therefore, reporting under NPRI Part 3 was\r\nnot required.\r\nThe facility did not meet the screening criteria for NPRI Part 4 CACs, since employees worked less than\r\n20,000 hours at the facility in 2022. Facility records indicate that none of the Part 4 NPRI contaminants\r\nthat had on-site releases to air exceeded their release-based thresholds."
        }
    ],
